The Nigerian troops deployed in Operation Last Hold have been advised to keep to the rules of engagement while carrying out their assigned duties of clearing the North East of Boko Haram terrorists. The Acting General Officer Commanding (GOC) 7 Division, Brigadier General Abdulmalik Bulama Biu gave the advice yesterday while addressing  troops  at Gemtillo, Maiduguri. In a statement signed by the Director Army Public Relations, Brigadier General Texas Chukwu he added that the Acting GOC charged the troops to put in their best towards ending the Boko Haram Terrorists menace in that region. The charge is coming on the heels of several criticism and allegations concerning the conduct of the operations by the Nigerian Army Troops in the North East. Brigadier General Abdulmalik Bulama Biu  said that he was in the camp to motivate the troops and expressed delight with their state of  morale. He added that a lot has been achieved by the troops of Operation Lafiya Dole on ground and urged them to maintain the momentum. General Biu further advised the troops to shun any acts that would distract them from attaining their objective. He  was accompanied during the visit  by some Principal Staff Officers of the Division.